_Aeromonas hydrophila_ is a bacterium that causes illness in a wide 
range of organisms. However, in 2009, a new strain of this bacteria 
(ML09-119) was isolated from a series of disease outbreaks in channel 
catfish aquaculture farms of Alabama. The disease spread across the 
state of Mississippi within the next five years. Then in 2014, 
**another** new strain of the bacteria was isolated from channel catfish 
in the Mississippi Delta region (S14-452)! 


Dealing with multiple strains of a bacteria can prove difficult with 
creating vaccines or administering antibiotics so we wanted to see how 
the temporal distribution of these two strains compared. So, we analyzed 
the isolates from various cases using polymerase chain reaction (PCR) 
and electrophoresis. The image below shows what a typical
